# All patterns below are root-anchored (leading slash). Unanchored directory
# names (e.g. bare "Queue/") match at ANY depth in gitignore semantics — on a
# case-insensitive filesystem (macOS default, core.ignorecase=true) that
# silently swallows same-named nested paths too, e.g. claude/skills/queue/
# would vanish under a bare "Queue/" rule with no error, no signal. Anchor
# everything; this is exactly the silent-drift failure mode the track-list
# guard exists to catch — the ignore-list itself must not reintroduce it.

# === Created Content (operator's living knowledge layer — never published) ===
/Knowledge/
/Data/
/Contexts/
/Attachments/
/Queue/
/Working/

# === Operational State (queue/backlog artifacts) ===
/backlog.json
/backlog-archive.json

# === Private Configuration ===
/CLAUDE.md
/claude/settings.local.json
/claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# === Instance data embedded in an otherwise-public contract doc ===
# Real colleague/employer names — see the file's own frontmatter Publication note.
# Never mirror this content anywhere git-tracked.
/spec/tag-taxonomy-rosters.md

# === Symlink (local infrastructure, not tracked) ===
/.claude

# === Operator PII rules (symlink -> ~/bin/dotty-private/gitleaks-operator-rules.toml) ===
/.gitleaks-operator-rules.toml

# === Unsanitized eval fixtures (HOLD status — real/unscrubbed content, per
# {workspace_root}/System/Context/wiki-publication-boundary-map.md > Decisions #4) ===

# === Transient markers (any depth is fine/intended for this one) ===
.DS_Store

# Evals never publish (no estate repo ships evals — operator convention)
/Evals/
